{"title_page": "Nemat Mokhtarzada", "text_new": "{{Other people|Nemat|Nemat (disambiguation)){{!}}Nemat}}\n\n'''Nemat Mokhtarzada''' (Dari:  \u0646\u0639\u0645\u062a \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647 \u0645\u062e\u062a\u0627\u0631\u0632\u0627\u062f\u0647) is a well-known modern [[Afghanistan|Tajik]] poet from Afghanistan. He writes regularly for many Afghan magazines and newspapers in [[Germany]] and the [[United States]]. He appeared in [[Madar TV]] hosted by Mastora Hashemi in Germany. He has also written many lyrics for [[Sami Rafi]], a classical Tajik poet and singer of Afghanistan.\n\n==External links==\n*[https://www.samerafi.com Same Rafi's website]\n*[http://afgazad.com/Adabi.htm Free Afghanistan Magazine]\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Mokhtarzada, Nemat}}\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:Persian-language poets]]\n[[Category:Afghan Tajik people]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Afghan poets]]\n[[Category:Afghan Bah\u00e1'\u00eds]]\n[[Category:Converts to the Bah\u00e1'\u00ed Faith]]\n[[Category:20th-century Bah\u00e1'\u00eds]]\n[[Category:21st-century Bah\u00e1'\u00eds]]\n[[Category:Tajik poets]]\n", "text_old": "{{Other people|Nemat|Nemat (disambiguation)){{!}}Nemat}}\n\n'''Nemat Mokhtarzada''' (Dari:  \u0646\u0639\u0645\u062a \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647 \u0645\u062e\u062a\u0627\u0631\u0632\u0627\u062f\u0647) is a well-known modern [[Afghanistan|Tajik]] poet from Afghanistan. He writes regularly for many Afghan magazines and newspapers in [[Germany]] and the [[United States]]. He appeared in [[Madar TV]] hosted by Mastora Hashemi in Germany. He has also written many lyrics for [[Sami Rafi]], a classical Tajik poet and singer of Afghanistan.\n\n==External links==\n*[https://www.samerafi.com Same Rafi's website]\n*[http://afgazad.com/Adabi.htm Free Afghanistan Magazine]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Mokhtarzada, Nemat}}\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:Persian-language poets]]\n[[Category:Afghan Tajik p