 Reich Chancellery and F\u00fchrerbunker Complex]]. An Illustrated History of the Seat of the Nazi Regime | publisher=McFarland | location=Jefferson, NC | isbn=978-0-7864-2393-4 | ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book | last=Linge | first=Heinz | authorlink=Heinz Linge | year=2009 | title=With Hitler to the End | publisher=Frontline Books\u2013Skyhorse Publishing | location=London; New York | isbn=978-1-60239-804-7 | ref=harv | url=https://archive.org/details/withhitlertoendm00ling }}\n* {{cite book | last = McNab | first = Chris | title = Hitler's Masterplan: The Essential Facts and Figures for Hitler's Third Reich | publisher = Amber Books Ltd | year = 2011 | isbn = 978-1907446962 | ref=harv }}\n* {{cite book | last = McNab | first = Chris | title = Hitler's Fortresses: German Fortifications and Defences 1939\u201345 | publisher = Osprey Publishing | location = Oxford; New York | year = 2014 | isbn = 978-1-78200-828-6 | ref=harv}}\n* {{cite journal | last=Mollo | first=Andrew | year=1988 | editor-last=Ramsey | editor-first=Winston | title=The Berlin F\u00fchrerbunker: The Thirteenth Hole | journal=After the Battle | issue=61 | publisher=Battle of Britain International | location=London | ref=harv}}\n* {{cite web | author=MI5 staff | year=2005 | title=Hitler's last days | work=mi5.gov.uk | publisher=[[MI5]] | url=https://www.mi5.gov.uk/home/about-us/who-we-are/mi5-history/world-war-ii/hitlers-last-days.html | accessdate=12 June 2011 | ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book | last=Shirer | first=William L. | authorlink=William L. Shirer | year=1960 | title=[[The Rise and Fall of the Third Reich]] | publisher=Simon & Schuster | location=New York | isbn=978-0-671-62420-0 | ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book | last=Speer | first=Albert | authorlink=Albert Speer | origyear=1969 | year=1971 | title=[[Inside the Third Reich]] | publisher=Avon | location=New York | isbn=978-0-380-00071-5 | ref=harv}}\n* {{cite web | author = Staff | title = Debunking Hitler: Marking the Site of the F\u00fchrer's Bunker | work = [[Spiegel Online]] | publisher = Spiegel-Verlag | date = 9 June 2006 | url = http://www.spiegel.de/international/debunking-hitler-marking-the-site-of-the-fuehrer-s-bunker-a-420483.html | accessdate = 7 April 2014 | ref = {{sfnRef|''Der Spiegel''|2006}} }}\n* {{cite book | last = Taylor | first = Blaine | title = Hitler's Headquarters: From Beer Hall to Bunker, 1920\u20131945 | year = 2007 | publisher = Potomac | location = Dulles, Virginia | isbn = 978-1-57488-928-4 | ref = harv}}\n* {{cite book | last = Weale | first = Adrian | title = Army of Evil: A History of the SS | year = 2012 | place = New York | publisher = Caliber Printing | isbn = 978-0-451-23791-0 | ref = harv}}\n* {{cite book | last = Williams | first = Andrew | year = 2005 | title = D-Day to Berlin | publisher = [[Hodder & Stoughton|Hodder]] | isbn = 978-0-340-83397-1 | ref = harv | url-access = registration | url = https://archive.org/details/ddaytoberlin0000will }}\n* {{cite book | last=Ziemke | first=Earl F. | year=1969 | title=Battle For Berlin: End Of The Third Reich | publisher=MacDonald | location=London | oclc=253711605 | ref=harv}}\n{{refend}}\n\n'''Further reading'''\n* {{cite book | last=Boldt | first=Gerhard | year=1973 | title=Hitler: The Last Ten Days | publisher=Coward, McCann & Geoghegan | location = New York | isbn = 978-0-698-10531-7 }}\n* {{cite book | author = C.I.U. General Staff, Geographical Section | editor1-last = Ramsey | editor1-first = Winston G. | title = Berlin: Allied Intelligence Map of Key Buildings | publisher = After the Battle \u2013 Battle of Britain International | date = 1990 | isbn = 978-1-870067-33-1}}\n* {{cite book | last=Fest | first=Joachim | authorlink=Joachim Fest | year=2005 | title=Inside Hitler's Bunker: The Last Days of the Third Reich | publisher=Picador | location = New York | isbn=978-0-374-13577-5 }}\n* {{cite book | last=Junge | first=Traudl | authorlink=Traudl Junge | editor1-last=M\u00fcller | editor1-first=Melissa | title=Until the Final 